HEADWORD: Groschen
<hw>Grosch"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.]</ety>
<def>A small silver coin and money of account of Germany, worth about
two cents. It was discontinued in the new monetary system of the empire
and not subsequently used.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

